reviews.review: With what JJ Abraham’s had to work with after the 8th movie, he did a fine job bringing the saga full circle
This is the best of the new films! The most fun fast paced Star Wars film I’ve ever seen! A great conclusion to the Skywalker Saga!
A good conclusion to the movies.   Lots of tributes to the original 3 movies and loved all the cameos by the stars of the original movies.
Great ending to a trilogy, only complaint was I wish I had more of it. Another 30-40 minutes would have been great, but I am still pleased with the ending!

The Rise of Skywalker had its moments, but overall the story doesn't match with the original 6 movies. Rey is way to powerful and they shouldn't have brought back palpatine, which only diminished Anakin Skywalkers story and arc.
I still have no idea what this trilogy was all about.

As a  very dedicated Fan of star wars I'll say This is Just another  Sci-fi 2019 Standard movie,  not star wars. the only Good scenes was the nostalgic scenes from the original trilogy . Shame on you Disney.  Cringe Jokes all around the movie, Finn never told to rey what it wanted to say, emotional fellings with rey, rose, and the deserter Girl... Anoher Droid who always say dont touch me? For what reason that droid? he never was usefull , at the end was rey who tell the resistend wheres palpatine.

Great conclusion to a trilogy that had so much potential but misfired due to The Last Jedi.  If only JJ Abrams could have directed all three movies.  Abrams did a fantastic job giving fans what they want and doing his best to tie up the loose ends that The Last Jedi created.  I feel that he truly understands what makes Star Wars special to so many, and didn't try and take it in some crazy direction of his own.  I thought the Rise of Skywalker was very well done and helped me find new love for the newer movies of the franchise. I left the theater feeling really good this time, unlike the feeling I had after seeing The Last Jedi.
I thought it was really well paced. This movie felt like star wars. The characters felt like they had some development that mattered. Every scene felt important.
